
[1]scorning

   SCORN'ING, ppr. Holding in great contempt; despising; disdaining.

   SCORN'ING, n. The act of contemning; a treating with contempt, slight
   or disdain.

   How long will the scorners delight in their scorning?

                              Prov. 1. Ps. 123.
